    <div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Nine traditions, north to south</p><h2>The regions</h2></div>
    <div class="region-list">
      <div class="region-row"><h3>Lombardy <span class="ita">(Lombardia)</span></h3><p class="region-meta">Milan &middot; Light&ndash;medium &middot; Fruit &amp; Floral</p><p class="region-desc">Italy&rsquo;s lightest, most aromatic style - smooth, with minimal bitterness.</p></div>
      <div class="region-row"><h3>Piedmont <span class="ita">(Piemonte)</span></h3><p class="region-meta">Turin &middot; Light&ndash;medium &middot; Sweet &amp; Chocolate</p><p class="region-desc">A milk-and-cocoa culture; the <span class="ita">bicerin</span> - espresso, chocolate, cream - began here in the 18th century.</p></div>
      <div class="region-row"><h3>Trieste</h3><p class="region-meta">Friuli &middot; Medium &middot; Fruit &amp; Floral / Sweet &amp; Chocolate</p><p class="region-desc">Italy&rsquo;s historic coffee port and a Mitteleuropean roasting tradition - gentler than the south.</p></div>
      <div class="region-row is-here"><h3>Tuscany <span class="ita">(Toscana)</span> <span class="region-here">Where we are now</span></h3><p class="region-meta">Medium &middot; Sweet &amp; Chocolate</p><p class="region-desc">Family <span class="ita">torrefazioni</span> and the balanced middle of the national spectrum. Our founding region.</p></div>
      <div class="region-row"><h3>Lazio</h3><p class="region-meta">Rome &middot; Medium-dark &middot; Bold &amp; Spiced</p><p class="region-desc">Pulled <span class="ita">ristretto</span> - toasty, dark-caramel, with a spice note from centuries of trade.</p></div>
      <div class="region-row"><h3>Campania</h3><p class="region-meta">Naples &middot; Dark &middot; Bold &amp; Spiced</p><p class="region-desc">The archetype of &ldquo;strong Italian coffee&rdquo; - thick crema, bold and bitter, served very hot.</p></div>
      <div class="region-row"><h3>Puglia</h3><p class="region-meta">Dark &middot; Bold &amp; Spiced</p><p class="region-desc">Strong, low-acidity, and robusta-forward.</p></div>
      <div class="region-row"><h3>Calabria</h3><p class="region-meta">Very dark &middot; Bold &amp; Spiced</p><p class="region-desc">The darkest, most intense style on the mainland.</p></div>
      <div class="region-row"><h3>Sicily <span class="ita">(Sicilia)</span></h3><p class="region-meta">Dark &middot; Bold &amp; Spiced / Sweet &amp; Chocolate</p><p class="region-desc">A dark roast tied to almond and <span class="ita">granita</span> coffee culture - it reads sweeter than the Calabrian and Neapolitan extreme.</p></div>
    </div>
    <p class="afd">Region describes where a coffee is <strong>roasted</strong> - a Crema Italia curatorial choice - not where the bean was <strong>grown</strong>. Our catalog grows one region at a time; today, that is Tuscany.</p>
  </main>
</div>

